353.4	Machinima	Machinima	Machinima ( or ) is the use of real-time 3D computer graphics rendering engines to create a cinematic production. Most often, video games are used to generate the computer animation. Machinima-based artists, sometimes called machinimists or machinimators, are often fan laborers, by virtue of their re-use of copyrighted materials (see below).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d1/Diary_of_a_Camper.jpg/220px-Diary_of_a_Camper.jpg
